    "summary": "Wim Wijnen is an independent researcher and consultant at W2Economics, and a leading international expert in economic analysis of road safety. As a consultant he has performed projects on road safety and economics for clients such as the OECD, Asian Development Bank, World Bank, UNDP, Ministry of Infrastructure Netherlands, Delft University of Technology, SWOV, NGOs and private companies. Wim has worked in several countries, including low and middle-income countries. His work has been published in a large number of (scientific) publications, and he has been an (invited) speaker at many international conferences, seminars and workshops. He is also active as a guest lecturer at universities.\n\nSpecialisms: costs of road crashes, cost-benefit and cost-effectiveness analysis, economic  valuation of safety and health, impact of economic growth on road safety, financing road safety measures, effectiveness of road safety measures, health impact of injuries, quality/disability adjusted life years (QALYs, DALYs)",
