                    "company": "W2Economics",
                    "description": "Research and consultancy on road safety and economics. Recent projects:\n\n- SafetyCube: developing a decision support system for road safety, EC funded. Responsible for assessment of road crash costs in all EU member states and cost-benefit analysis tool.\n\n- Cost-benefit analysis 30 km/h roads: developing a flexible cost-benefit tool to assess traffic calming on urban roads.\n\n- Costs road crashes Netherlands: assessment of scenarios for a new cost study in the Netherlands, including international cooperation, for the Ministry of Infrastructure. With CE Delft.\n\n- Health and socio-economic impacts of cycling: an assessment of all relevant health impacts (physical exercise, exposure to emissions, road safety) in terms of DALYs and costs/benefits.\n\n- Impact of economic growth on road safety: an extensive survey of literature as part of the OECD-study \u2018Why does road safety improve when economic times are hard\u2019. With VU University.\n\n- Cost of road crashes for municipalities: an assessment of financial consequences of road crashes for Dutch municipalities.\n\n- Financing new road safety measures: an exploration of opportunities to fund new road safety measures, aimed at achieving road safety targets for 2020.\n\n- Costs of road crashes in Kazakhstan:  a comprehensive study into the socio-economic costs of road crashes, including a willingness to pay survey, showing that costs are 3.5% of GDP.\n\n- Cost-benefit analysis of contour marking on trucks: an analysis of road safety impacts, costs and benefits of contour marking, for 3M Belgium. In cooperation with SWOV.\n\nOther activities:\n- Guest lecturer at Delft Road Safety Courses, NOVI Traffic Academy and Delft University of Technology\n- Member working group \u2018Road Safety Economics\u2019 of FERSI (Forum of European Road Safety Research Institutes)",
                    "title": "Independent researcher/consultant",
                    "employment_type": null
                }
            ]
